headline: SEC Punts on BlackRock Ethereum ETF Staking, Franklin XRP and Solana Fund Decisions
summary: The SEC pushed off whether to allow staking for the iShares Ethereum ETF, and on proposed Franklin Templeton funds tracking Solana and XRP.

headline: Oracle Surge Lifts S&P 500 to New Record
summary: A breakneck rally in  Oracle  shares helped power the S&P 500 to another record, while a slide in  Apple  dragged down the Dow Jones Industrial Average.  The Wall Street Journal reported Wednesday afternoon that OpenAI and Oracle signed a $300 billion computing deal, among the biggest cloud contracts ever signed.  Oracle added $247 billion in market value, surpassing  JPMorgan Chase  to become the 10th-largest company by market capitalization, according to Dow Jones Market Data.

headline: CBOE Targets Traders With Mag10 Futures, Options
summary: CBOE Global Markets Inc. will offer traders a new way to bet on mega-cap technology stocks with futures and options based on the CBOE Magnificent 10 Index. CBOE Global Markets Executive Vice President, Global Head of Derivatives Catherine Clay has more on the story.

headline: Cboe Plans to Launch Cash-Settled Futures and Options on New Index Tracking Tech and Growth-Orientated U.S. Stocks
summary: Cboe Global Markets, Inc. (Cboe: CBOE), the world's leading derivatives and securities exchange network, today announced plans to launch futures and options on the new Cboe Magnificent 10 Index, subject to regulatory review. The new product suite will offer investors a way to gain targeted exposure to several of the most actively traded AI technology-focused stocks through cash-settled index futures and options.

headline: Will Cboe Global Markets’ (CBOE) Data Integration Shape Its Advantage in the Evolving Broker Landscape?
summary: Centroid Solutions recently announced the completion of its integration with Cboe Global Markets' U.S. and European market data feeds, enabling brokers direct access to real-time data across equities, options, indices, and derivatives. This collaboration broadens Cboe's data services reach, potentially benefitting both trading efficiency and client service for brokers connected through Centroid's platform.
